What is Web Scraping:-----

Web Scraping means automatically extracting data from websites.

Example:
Extract data like:

Product prices

News headlines

Job listings

Weather data

Instead of manually copying data, a Python script collects it automatically.

Example website data:

Product	Price
Laptop	₹50000
Mobile	₹20000


2️ What is Data Extraction:----

Data Extraction means retrieving useful information from any data source such as:

Websites

PDFs

Databases

APIs

Logs

Example:

Extract emails from web pages

Extract tables from HTML

Extract data from PDF reports

Web scraping is one type of data extraction.

-- Python Tools for Web Scraping
1️BeautifulSoup

Used for HTML parsing.

Install:

pip install beautifulsoup4
pip install requests

Example:

import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup

url = "https://example.com"

response = requests.get(url)

soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, "html.parser")

title = soup.title.text

print("Page Title:", title)

Output:

Page Title: Example Domain
2️Scrapy:---

A powerful framework for large scraping projects.

Install:

pip install scrapy

Create project:

scrapy startproject myproject

Run spider:

scrapy crawl spidername
3️ Selenium:----

Used when websites load data using JavaScript.

Install:

pip install selenium

Example:

from selenium import webdriver

driver = webdriver.Chrome()

driver.get("https://example.com")

print(driver.title)

driver.quit()
4️Puppeteer (Node.js):---

You already used Puppeteer in your Docker scraping project, which is great for scraping dynamic websites.

---Web Scraping Workflow
Website
   ↓
HTTP Request (requests)
   ↓
HTML Page
   ↓
Parse HTML (BeautifulSoup)
   ↓
Extract Data
   ↓
Save Data (CSV / JSON / Database)

from bs4 import BeautifulSoup

url = "https://news.ycombinator.com"

response = requests.get(url)

soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, "html.parser")

titles = soup.find_all("span", class_="titleline")

for title in titles:
    print(title.text)

data = ["News1", "News2", "News3"]

with open("news.csv", "w") as file:
    writer = csv.writer(file)
    for item in data:
        writer.writerow([item])


